15/07/2008
ATHENS, Greece â An earthquake measuring 6.3 on the Richter scale shook the Greek island of Rhodes early Tuesday (July 15th). 
A woman slipped on some steps while trying to escape her home and died. 
The tremor's epicentre was localised in the sea south of the island, 445km east of Athens. 
Citizens felt the quake throughout Rhodes, Crete, Santorini and Samos, as well as in Cyprus. 
Authorities reported no major damage apart from one landslide and a series of blackouts. 
(ANA-MPA, ERT, In.news, Kathimerini, Naftemporiki, SKAI, CNA, Philelefteros - 15/07/08)
